==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Synonymize
<hw>Syn*on"y*mize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Synonymized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Synonymizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To
express by a synonym or synonyms; to give the synonym or synonyms
corresponding to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This word ⟦ldquo⟧fortis⟦rdquo⟧ we may <qex>synonymize</qex> after
all these fashions: stout, hardy, valiant, doughty, courageous,
adventurous, brave, bold, daring, intrepid.</q>
<rj><qau>Camden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Synonymous</ent>⟦br⟧
